<statement>
<p>Solve the equation: <m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{{7}{x}}}\right)}-{10}={0}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=</m><fillin characters="6" /> </p>
<p>Round to 3 decimal places.</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>0.057</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{{7}{x}}}\right)}-{10}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{\left({10}^{{{7}{x}}}\right)}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{{7}{x}}}=-\frac{{10}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={\log{{\left(-\frac{{10}}{{4}}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{\log{{\left(-\frac{{10}}{{4}}\right)}}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}\approx{0.057}</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

